<FIRST>r a PM-APAppointment     05-04 0137</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-AP Appointment,0140</SECOND>
<HEAD>AP Bureau Chief Named in Virginia</HEAD>
<DATELINE>RICHMOND, Va. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Dorothy Gast Abernathy, correspondent in
charge of The Associated Press bureau in Cleveland for the past two
years, will return to Virginia as AP's chief of bureau in Richmond.
   The appointment was announced Wednesday by Louis D. Boccardi,
president of the news cooperative.
   Ms. Abernathy, 33, who was Roanoke correspondent from 1983 to
1987, will direct AP operations in Richmond, Norfolk and Roanoke.
She succeeds Dennis Montgomery, who resigned.
   Ms. Abernathy joined the AP in Little Rock, Ark., in 1982 and
was named correspondent in Roanoke the following year. She became
Cleveland correspondent in 1987.
   She is a native of St. Henry, Ohio, and a graduate of Ohio State
University. She began her journalism career as a reporter with the
Kansas City Star.
</TEXT>
