<FIRST>d a PM-BRF--Nailed     05-04 0123</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-BRF--Nailed,0128</SECOND>
<HEAD>Police Nail Suspect in Salon Holdups</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Police said they nailed a suspect in a series of
manicure-salon holdups after a victim fingered him.
   Richard A. Cobbs, 25, was suspected in the gunpoint robberies of
about 10 Lexington Avenue salons that netted about $5,000 in cash
and goods during the past few weeks, police said.
   He was arrested Wednesday after a woman whose salon had been
robbed spotted him on Lexington Avenue and called police.
   ``Our guys were right around the corner,'' said Lt. Donald
DeBellis, commander of the Manhattan Robbery Squad.
   Cobbs was unarmed and gave no resistance. Several salon holdup
victims identified him in lineups, and he was arrested on charges
of robbery, police said.
</TEXT>
