<FIRST>r i PM-BRF--Brazil-Miners     05-04 0117</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-BRF--Brazil-Miners,0118</SECOND>
<HEAD>30 Gold Miners Die In Amazon Mudslide</HEAD>
<DATELINE>RIO DE JANEIRO, Brazil (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   At least 30 gold miners died when
a 200-foot wall of mud surrounding their excavation site collapsed
and buried them in the remote Amazon jungle, authorities said.
   Vera Lucia Batista, of the State Secretary for Public Security,
said the disaster occurred Tuesday following heavy rains at Buraco
Fundo, more than 3,800 miles northwest of Rio, near the Venezuelan
border.
   Ms. Batista said by telephone that three survivors informed
police at least 30 miners had been buried alive. She said a team of
police officials was sent to the area by helicopter and that a
search for bodies was still going on.
</TEXT>
