<HEAD>Networks Plan Live Shuttle Coverage</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Four television networks planned live coverage
of today's scheduled launch of the space shuttle Atlantis.
   NASA planned to launch the space shuttle from Cape Canaveral,
Fla., at 1:48 p.m. A launch Friday was canceled 31 seconds before
liftoff because of a short circuit in a fuel pump.
   CBS planned to break into its regular programming at 1:39 p.m.
for about 10 minutes. NBC planned to begin its report at 1:40 p.m.,
and CNN, the cable network, was to begin its shuttle coverage at
