<HEAD>Train Derails 400 Miles Northwest of Mexico City, 8 Dead</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TEPIC, Mexico (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A passenger train derailed about 400 miles
northwest of Mexico City, killing at least eight people and
injuring another 50, the government news agency Notimex said.
   The agency quoted railroad officials as saying the accident
Wednesday afternoon just north of this Nayarit state capital
occurred on a train that was bound for the border city of Nogales,
70 miles south of Tucson, Ariz.
   It was the second serious train accident in Mexico in as many
days.
   On Tuesday evening, at least 20 people suffered minor injuries
when a passenger train plowed into a parked locomotive outside the
station in Mexicali, across the border from Calexico, Calif.
