<FIRST>r a PM-ChildFall     05-04 0256</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Child Fall,0265</SECOND>
<HEAD>Toddler Falls 9 Stories, Saved By Juniper Bush</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DENVER (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A 2-year-old girl fell nine stories from an open
window, but landed in a springy juniper bush and survived.
   ``I have owies,'' says Heather Ruebush. She was listed in good
condition today at University Hospital, where she was treated for a
lacerated liver, two broken ribs and scratches.
   ``She's a miracle baby, definitely,'' said her mother, Katrina
Tellus. ``They're calling her the bouncing miracle baby around the
hospital.''
   Heather was moved from intensive care to a regular ward
Wednesday and was expected to stay for observation through the
weekend.
   Heather, her mother and a friend had returned home from shopping
Monday and Tellus began preparing dinner.
   She said she was unaware that a living room window was open, its
sill about a foot above the floor.
   ``I turned around, and she wasn't there. It happened that
quick,'' said Tellus, 22. ``I was just praying to God she didn't go
through that window. When I saw that open window, it was complete
fright.
   ``She either sat on the window still and leaned back, or she
dropped her bottle and went after it. I've asked her, but she
doesn't know what happened.''
   Tellus said she ran to the window and looked down to where
Heather had landed in a 3-foot-tall juniper bush.
   ``She was down there, sitting up,'' Tellus said. ``She stayed
conscious all the time.''
   ``She said `Mama,''' Tellus said. ``She was kind of fading in
and out. She was just whimpering.''
</TEXT>
