<DATELINE>CHICAGO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A grand jury considering whether to return a
murder charge against a man who unhooked the life-support system
from his comatose infant son heard testimony from the defendant's
wife and two other family members.
   Rudy Linares, 23, of suburban Cicero, is charged by police with
murdering his 16-month-old son, Samuel, on April 26 at a Chicago
