nine months before when he swallowed a piece of a balloon, choked
and fell into an irreversible coma.
   Prosecutors and defense attorneys refused to divulge what was
said at the closed hearing.
   If the grand jury chooses not to return an indictment, the case
probably would be referred to a Circuit Court judge, whose options
would include dropping the existing charge.
