<HEAD>Navy Ships Foil Alleged Communist Attempt To Seize Fishing Boat</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SEOUL, South Korea (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   South Korean navy ships on Thursday
foiled an apparent North Korean attempt to seize a South Korean
fishing boat near the western sea border, the Defense Ministry said.
   A North Korean naval craft tried to seize the 23-ton Samjin-ho
operating in the area, the ministry said.
   The North Korean ship retreated to the north when South Korean
navy ships chased it, the ministry said.
