<FIRST>r i AM-BRF--KillerCrocodile     05-04 0132</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--Killer Crocodile,0135</SECOND>
<HEAD>Reptile Attacks, Kills Fisherman</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BULAWAYO, Zimbabwe (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A fisherman was attacked and
apparently devoured by a crocodile while swimming in the Zambezi
River in northern Zimbabwe, witnesses said Thursday.
   Sean Geasley, 24, who lived in Zimbabwe's second-biggest city of
Bulawayo, ignored warnings that the river was crocodile-infested
and dived into a pool, according to witnesses.
   About 230 feet out, Geasley cried ``Ouch!'' twice before
disappearing beneath the surface, workmate Dennis Green said.
   ``He did not cry out for help or even call my name,'' Green
said. ``I think he must have been in a state of shock. Because I
was very far from him there was nothing I could do to help.''
   When police later combed the river no corpse was found.
Crocodiles usually devour their prey.
</TEXT>
