<DATELINE>FORT WORTH, Texas (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Pianist Van Cliburn says he will return
this year to the Soviet Union, the scene in 1958 of his first major
triumph.
   ``I am going to Russia,'' said Cliburn at a news conference
Wednesday at the downtown Petroleum Club. ``Whether it will be in
July or October, I don't know.''
   The lanky Texan said negotiations began after an invitation from
Raisa Gorbachev, wife of Soviet President Mikhail Gorbachev, for
