<DATELINE>CEDAR RAPID, Iowa (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Estelle Getty, who portrays an
outspoken octogenarian on NBC-TV's ``Golden Girls,'' joked with
hospitalized senior citizens and told them not to fade into the
woodwork.
   As the actress shook hands Wednesday with members of Mercy
Medical Center's Prime Timers group, Viola Wetzel of Cedar Rapids
revealed her age.
   ``You're 94?'' said Getty. ``You look better than I do!''
   Wetzel was surprised Getty is considerably younger than the
85-year-old Sophia Petrillo she portrays on TV.
   Getty, who is in her early 60s but won't disclose her age, says
the show's producers weren't sure they wanted a younger woman to
play Sophia.
   ``I told them, `Where are you ever going to find an 85-year-old
woman who will come in to work everyday?''' Getty said.
   ``If there's just one thing I hope the show and my character
tell you is that you can get older without growing old. There's no
need to fade into the woodwork when you reach 60 or 70 or 80.
You've got to keep at it.''
