<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Following is the text of a statement read by
Oliver North on Thursday after a federal court jury convicted him
on three counts and acquitted him on nine others in charges arising
from the Iran-Contra affair:
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
   
   ``Today's verdict by the jury here in Washington is a partial
vindication for what has been for my family and me a very long and
difficult process. Throughout this, my family and I have been
sustained by the support and the love and the kindness and the
prayers of the American people. Without them and their love, and
