<SECOND>AM-Rap Beating,0266</SECOND>
<HEAD>Man Beaten Into Coma After Argument Over Rap Singing</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TACOMA, Wash. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Two men beat a man into a coma after the
three had a drunken argument about who was the better rap singer,
police said.
   Willie Lee Walker, 34, was attacked by the two men with sticks
and a board and had a 20-pound concrete block dropped on his head
at least twice, said Tacoma Police spokesman Mark Mann.
   ``They just drank themselves silly and got into an argument,''
Mann said.
   Walker was comatose and in critical condition at Tacoma General
Hospital on Thursday, Mann said.
   A 25-year-old man was arrested Wednesday for investigation of
aggravated assault but was not immediately charged, police said.
   The attack took place early Wednesday morning after the three
argued at the apartment of one of the suspects.
   Walker was found in the entrance to an alley by police who
responded to calls from neighborhood residents, but his assailants
had fled by the time police and medical assistance arrived.
   Detectives followed a trail of blood from the crime scene to the
apartment. The arrested man was found to have cut and bloody
knuckles, and blood-stained clothes and shoes were found in the
apartment, police said.
   The suspect told detectives the three men spent Tuesday night
and early Wednesday morning drinking, and an argument over who was
the better rapper developed into a fistfight, Mann said. Walker ran
from the apartment and the two other men gave chase, Mann said.
   The second assailant was not identitied, Mann said.
