<HEAD>With BC-AP Arts: Franklin</HEAD>
<HEAD>Aretha Franklin's Grammy Awards</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Here is a list of Grammy Awards won by Aretha
Franklin:
   _ 1967: Best R&amp;B Record, ``Respect.''
   _ 1967: Best R&amp;B Solo Performance, ``Respect.''
   _ 1968: Best Female R&amp;B Vocal Performance, ``Chain of Fools.''
   _ 1969: Best Female R&amp;B Vocal Performance, ``Share Your Love
With Me.''
   _ 1970: Best Female R&amp;B Vocal Performance, ``Don't Play That
Song.''
   _ 1971: Best Female R&amp;B Vocal Performance, ``Bridge Over
Troubled Water.''
   _ 1972: Best Female R&amp;B Vocal Performance, ``Young, Gifted and
Black.''
   _ 1972: Best Female Soul Gospel Performance, ``Amazing Grace.''
   _ 1973: Best Female R&amp;B Vocal Performance, ``Master of Eyes.''
   _ 1974: Best Female R&amp;B Vocal Performance, ``Ain't Nothing Like
the Real Thing.''
   _ 1981: Best Female R&amp;B Vocal Performance, ``Hold On, I'm
Coming.''
   _ 1985: Best Female R&amp;B Vocal Performance, ``Freeway of Love.''
   _ 1987: Best Female R&amp;B Vocal Performance, ``Aretha.''
   _ 1987: Best R&amp;B Performance by a Duo; ``I Knew You Were
Waiting,'' a duet with George Michael.
   _ 1988: Best Female Soul Gospel Performance, ``One Lord, One
Faith, One Baptism.''
</TEXT>
