<FIRST>u f BC-Britain-Stocks     05-04 0178</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Britain-Stocks,0186</SECOND>
<HEAD>London Share Prices Sharply Higher At Midday</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Share prices were sharply higher at midday
Thursday, with prices of selected issues marked up as a bit of
institutional buying interest caught market makers short of stock.
   At about 12:15 p.m., the Financial Times-Stock Exchange
100-share index was up 17.4 points, or 0.8 percent, at 2,123.1, its
best level of the day. At its lowest, the index was up 10.6 points
shortly after the opening.
   Volume came to 321.9 million shares by midday, compared with
234.7 million shares at the same time Wednesday.
   Dealers generally were surprised by the market's performance,
which had been expected to continue its recent dull tone, at least
until Friday's report on U.S. employment for April.
   ``Personally I find it very difficult to see why the market
should have a bull run at the moment,'' said an equities salesman
for a leading British brokerage firm.
   ``It's a combination of just a little bit of buying interest and
a market where there isn't very much stock around,'' added another
salesman.
</TEXT>
