<HEAD>Production Goes Down This Week</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Domestic automakers were scheduled to produce
242,655 cars and light trucks this week, down from last week's
250,782, Ward's Automotive Reports said Thursday.
   This week's production is lower than the same week a year ago,
in which 249,667 cars and light trucks were produced, the trade
journal said.
   U.S. automakers were scheduled to make 154,930 cars this week,
compared with 162,922 a week ago and 160,826 in the same week in
1988.
   Light truck production for the week was scheduled at 87,725,
compared with last week's 87,860 and last year's 88,841.
   Canadian automakers were to build 21,245 cars this week, up from
20,272 a week ago but down from last year's 26,727.
   Canadian light truck production was scheduled at 21,427,
compared with 21,312 a week ago and 20,634 in the same week last
year.
